{
  "texts": [
    "Rather than taking on a communicative function, her gaze is part of an introspective process, which Jording and colleagues (2018) describe as \"attentional disengagement from the outside world,\" while a person neither \"focuses on objects nor persons in the environment but only on his (sic!)",
    "inner experience\" (p. 4).",
    "I would not so much say that Paula disengages from an 'outside world.'",
    "Rather, she is conneceting past experiences to current circumstances.",
    "In doing so, she begins to mold her own cognitive ecology (Hutchins 2010; Tribble and Sutton 2011)."
  ]
}